cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.NA 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with finding nonoverlapping balls in a metric space, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes an algorithm for finding the optimum set of balls in a metric space, which involves designing efficient data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper formulates the problem as a linear program and its dual, which involves discrete optimization techniques. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper proposes an algorithm for finding a minimum-weight set of cycles covering all vertices in a complete geometric graph, which is a problem in game theory. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper deals with finding the optimum set of balls in a metric space, which involves numerical optimization techniques.
